President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Arnold A. Chacon, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Guatemala. Christopher Merrill, director of the International Writing Program at the University of Iowa, is nominated for Member of the National Council on the Humanities. Earl Anthony Wayne, currently the Deputy Ambassador to Afghanistan, is nominated for Ambassador to the United Mexican States. Rebecca R. Wodder, President and CEO of American Rivers, is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Fish and Wildlife at the Department of the Interior. Additionally, Giselle Fernandez is appointed to the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Fernandez is the Managing Director of Creative World Talent Management and has a background in journalism.